<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="_1Ni-INnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="review_requirements,{FEC5ED66-F467-4BD5-AB11-B300E101DB9B}" guid="_1Ni-INnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" changeDate="2005-10-05T07:44:22.369-0700" version="7.1.0">
  <sections xmi:id="_PUvJcNnnEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="General Recommendations " guid="_PUvJcNnnEdmO6L4XMImrsA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;GeneralRecommendations&quot; name=&quot;GeneralRecommendations&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;table&#xD;
    style=&quot;BORDER-RIGHT: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid; BORDER-TOP: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid; BORDER-LEFT: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid&quot;&#xD;
     cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; bordercolordark=&quot;#808080&quot; cellpadding=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; bordercolorlight=&quot;#808080&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;tbody>&#xD;
            &lt;tr>&#xD;
                &lt;td width=&quot;5%&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>Purpose&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/td>&#xD;
                &lt;td width=&quot;95%&quot;>&#xD;
                    General recommendations for each review.&#xD;
                &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
    &lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following guidelines are helpful when reviewing the results of Requirements:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Always conduct reviews in a meeting format, although the meeting participants might prepare some reviews on their&#xD;
        own.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Continuously check what is produced to make sure the quality is as high as possible. Checklists are provided for&#xD;
        this purpose; refer to the checklist for each work product. You can use them for informal review meetings or in&#xD;
        daily work.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The reviews should concentrate on the requirements currently being developed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following roles will participate in the review meetings:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_technical_reviewer_81F699C8.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{0319C70C-35C9-4190-94F0-E7E5E9216CA0}&quot;>Requirements Reviewer&lt;/a>:&amp;nbsp;A person acting as a requirements&#xD;
        reviewer has some essential knowledge of the business or technology domain and detailed knowledge of the applied&#xD;
        facilitation and modeling techniques&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_requirement_specifier_A2500152.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{7264A534-7509-4B4B-AF73-CAECC0178898}&quot;>Requirements Specifier&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_system_analyst_C3C9C9AC.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{F1F206DF-3AA0-4AC0-92EF-8E4A01B6C5B5}&quot;>System Analyst&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You should also consider the following roles for participation in review meetings, especially at key milestones:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_stakeholder_1011D446.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{7A4262EA-AB5B-431E-BB4A-3822FBF7F239}&quot;>Stakeholders - customers and users&lt;/a> (Where possible)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_change_manager_51E43456.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{C1D3C2C0-15A0-49AD-9788-8C163E53CB96}&quot;>Change Control Manager&lt;/a> (Where reviewing Change Requests)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_test_designer_5F59E64F.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{84F723B5-288F-4AC4-B6C1-C75A07BFEEED}&quot;>Test Designer&lt;/a> (Optional)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_software_architect_DB0BF177.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{4AC346F0-E6FC-4D2C-8410-2EDF8DDDC91D}&quot;>Software Architect&lt;/a> (Optional, usually early in the software&#xD;
        lifecycle when the software architecture is under development)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/roles/rup_project_manager_363CE680.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{EE97A8CD-66CA-4A9B-9871-E3B94CCED528}&quot;>Project Manager&lt;/a> (Optional, usually during the early parts of the&#xD;
        the lifecycle, or when major changes are being reviewed)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is important to find the right balance between including the desired review participants and keeping the review&#xD;
    manageable and productive. Care should be taken to include only those participants who will contribute to achieving the&#xD;
    objectives of the review. It is usually more productive to hold several focused review sessions with a smaller number&#xD;
    of participants, than to hold one review involving many.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_PUvJcdnnEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="Recommended Review Meetings " guid="_PUvJcdnnEdmO6L4XMImrsA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;RecommendedReviewMeetings&quot; name=&quot;RecommendedReviewMeetings&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;table&#xD;
    style=&quot;BORDER-RIGHT: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid; BORDER-TOP: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid; BORDER-LEFT: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: rgb(128,128,128) 1px solid&quot;&#xD;
     cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; bordercolordark=&quot;#808080&quot; cellpadding=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; bordercolorlight=&quot;#808080&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;tbody>&#xD;
            &lt;tr>&#xD;
                &lt;td width=&quot;5%&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>Purpose&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/td>&#xD;
                &lt;td width=&quot;95%&quot;>&#xD;
                    To define the scope and the goals of the review.&lt;br />&#xD;
                     To define the approaches used for each specific scope/goal combination.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
                &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
    &lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Normally, you should divide the review into the following meetings:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A review of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_change_request_F2E6419.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{694A7BC8-3D20-4172-BC56-6C7BD4590BA5}&quot;>change requests&lt;/a> which impact the existing requirements set.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A review for each of the key requirements work products.&amp;nbsp; If the system is large, break this review into&#xD;
        several meetings, possibly one per key functional area.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Even if you can review everything at the same meeting, you probably won't get approval of your conclusions the first&#xD;
    time. Be prepared to carry out new reviews for each new version of the requirements work products.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_PUvJctnnEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="Prepare Review Record and Document Defects " guid="_PUvJctnnEdmO6L4XMImrsA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;PrepareReviewRecord&quot; name=&quot;PrepareReviewRecord&quot;>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;4&quot; style=&quot;border: 1px solid rgb(128,128,128)&quot;&#xD;
    bordercolorlight=&quot;#808080&quot; bordercolordark=&quot;#808080&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;5%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;b>Purpose&lt;/b>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;95%&quot;>&#xD;
                To document the review results.&lt;br />&#xD;
                 To ensure that identified defects are documented.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Following each review meeting, the results of the meeting are documented in a &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_review_record_CA816ECE.html&quot; guid=&quot;{4047B5B0-5FB7-4960-8A7E-451719D85DFF}&quot;>Review&#xD;
    Record&lt;/a>. In addition, any defects are documented in accordance with the project's change management process.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;FurtherReading&quot; name=&quot;FurtherReading&quot;>Further Reading&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    See: [&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/customcategories/references_56F06DFD.html#BIT03&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;7.755968586980351E-308&quot;>BIT03&lt;/a>] Chapter11.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_requirements__reviewing&quot; name=&quot;XE_requirements__reviewing&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this task is to formally verify that the results of the requirements tasks conform to the customer's&#xD;
    view of the system.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
